###Block: Basic Traits: Combat Traits
# Ability Name	Unique Key			Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																		Required Race	Description																																																																															Combat bonus					Add to base move							Source Page
Excitable
	KEY:Excitable ~ Trait
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait
	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Excitable ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]
	PRERACE:1,Gnome
	DESC:You demand that everything must happen right now, no matter what, and are too impatient to wait for everyone else to catch up. You finish people's sentences, blurt out the punch lines to slowly-told jokes, rarely make plans, and leap headlong into anything that looks like it might get interesting. While this has sometimes gotten you in trouble, it's also trained you to start moving a split second before everyone else, and that's saved your hide a few times as well.
	BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|3|TYPE=Trait
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.19

#Rapscallion		KEY:Rapscallion ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Rapscallion ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist|1|TYPE=Trait	BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|1|TYPE=Trait	DESC:You've spent your entire life thumbing your nose at the establishment, and you take pride in your run-ins with the law. Somehow, despite all the mischievous behavior in your life, you've never been caught-you always manage to stay one step ahead of your pursuers.		SOURCEPAGE:pg.19
Sprint
	KEY:Sprint ~ Trait
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait
	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sprint ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]
	PRERACE:1,Gnome
	DESC:You were taught from a young age that the world is full of big, fast, dangerous foes, and that sometimes the best course of action is to put your head down and run. Your parents taught you how to make the most of a solid mid-length sprint and how to squeeze just a little extra speed out of yourself.
	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|5|PREVARLT:ENCUMBERANCE,1
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.19



###Block: Basic Traits: Magic Traits
# Ability Name	Unique Key				Category of Ability		Type						Required AL				Multiple Requirements																			Required Race	Description																																																																																							Caster level							Source Page
Charlatan
	KEY:Charlatan ~ Trait
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait
	PREALIGN:NG,TN,NE,CG,CN,CE
	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Charlatan ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait]
	PRERACE:1,Gnome
	DESC:Your talent for illusion goes beyond a mere knack for figments and phantasms. You can actually channel spell energy into simple illusions that augment your attempts at deception. As a swift action, you may expend one prepared spell or spell slot to gain a bonus on the next Bluff check you make, provided the check takes place before the beginning of your next turn. The bonus on this check is equal to the level of the spell consumed. You may use this ability 3 times per day.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.19

Naturally Gifted
	KEY:Naturally Gifted ~ Trait
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait
	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Narurally Gifted ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait]
	PRERACE:1,Gnome
	DESC:For unknown reasons, you have deeper reserves of magical energy than those around you. Perhaps you are descended from a family of powerful arcane casters, or maybe you believe this trait marks you as destined for magical greatness. Wherever the truth lies, you gain an additional use of one of your gnome magic spell-like abilities each day. This does not always have to be the same spell-like ability-one day you might use dancing lights twice, only to use the additional casting for speak with animals the next day.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20

Trickster
	KEY:Trickster ~ Trait
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait
	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trickster ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait]
	PRERACE:1,Gnome
	DESC:You are particularly adept with your racial spell-like abilities, and as child you quickly learned how dancing lights and ghost sound could be used to amuse your friends and fool your elders. This natural talent for illusion continued as you grew older, and before long you were being offered training in more advanced figments and glamers. You gain a +1 trait bonus to your caster level when determining the duration, range, and area of all spells from the illusion school.
	BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SUBSCHOOL.Illusion|1|TYPE=Trait
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20



###Block: Basic Traits: Faith Traits
# Ability Name	Unique Key				Category of Ability		Type								Multiple Requirements																			Required Race	Required Text										Description																																																																																																																		Bonus to skill						Class Skill				Source Page
First Memories
	KEY:First Memories ~ Trait
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait.GnomeMagic
	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,First Memories ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]
	PRERACE:1,Gnome
	DESC:For your whole life, you've felt there was a world just beyond the fabric of the material objects around you, and sometimes you can hear the north wind calling you or smell the dread taint of polluted water before you taste it. You do not gain the normal list of spell-like abilities for the gnome magic racial trait presented in the Pathfinder RPG Core Rulebook. Instead, if you have a Wisdom of 11 of higher, you gain the following spell-like abilities: 1/day—detect poison, know direction, stabilize, and speak with animals. The caster level for these effects is equal to your character level. The DC for these spells is equal to 10 + the spell's level + your Wisdom modifier.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20

Zealot
	KEY:Zealot ~ Trait
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait
	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Zealot ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]
	PRERACE:1,Gnome
	PRETEXT:You must match the alignment of your chosen deity exactly.
	DESC:You aren't just faithful to the worship of your patron deity-you are obsessively loyal to all of the faith's tenets and guidelines. Your devotion is an anchor that keeps you from drifting away into the throes of the Bleaching, and you cling to it like the life raft it is. As long as you remain completely faithful to the tenets of your faith (as determined by the GM), you never suffer from the Bleaching.
	BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Religion)|1|TYPE=Trait
	CSKILL:Knowledge (Religion)
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20



